{
  "answer": "**In Cynewulf's *Juliana* (Chapter 1), after Juliana seizes and binds the demon who appeared to her as an angel in her prison cell, he confesses his role in tempting various historical persecutors of holy figures.**[^1]\n\nThe demon boasts of his involvement in the following events:\n\n- Inciting the soldier to pierce Jesus on the cross, causing blood and water to flow.[^1]\n- Whispering to Herod's heart to behead John the Baptist for rebuking his unlawful marriage.[^1]\n- Teaching Simon (Magus) to oppose Christ's apostles, calling them sorcerers.[^1]\n- Driving Nero to kill the apostles Peter and Paul.[^1]\n- Influencing Pilate to crucify Jesus.[^1]\n- Teaching Aegeas to crucify Andrew.[^1]\n\nHe then claims to have perpetrated countless other evils but cannot fully recount them.[^1]\n\nThis interrogation scene underscores the demon's long history of targeting saints and apostles, contrasting Juliana's steadfast faith.\n\n[^1]: Cynewulf, *Juliana*, [paragraph](/works/cynewulf-juliana-9a2157/01/translation/#p-da3fd4).",
